This Presidential Memorandum, issued on April 2, 2020, addresses the order of succession within the Pension Benefit Guaranty Corporation (PBGC). It states that in the event that the Director of the PBGC is unable to perform their duties, the Chief Financial Officer, Chief Management Officer, and General Counsel will act as and perform the functions and duties of the Director in that order. The memorandum also includes exceptions and revokes a previous Presidential Memorandum on the same subject. It clarifies that this memorandum does not affect the authority of executive departments or the functions of the Director of the Office of Management and Budget, and it should be implemented in accordance with applicable law and subject to available appropriations. Finally, the memorandum authorizes the publication of this document in the Federal Register.